data.enText: a priest of high rank who is in charge of the other priests in a cathedral

data.chText: （乡间主管若干教堂牧师的）主任牧师
data.enText: a priest who is in charge of the priests of several churches in an area
a person in a university who is in charge of a department of studies

data.chText: （大学，尤指牛津、剑桥大学的）学监
data.enText: (in a college or university, especially at Oxford or Cambridge) a person who is responsible for the discipline of students

means: (乡间主管若干教堂牧师的)主任牧师

tr: an administrator in charge of a division of a university or college
(Roman Catholic Church) the head of the College of Cardinals
a man who is the senior member of a group
example: he is the dean of foreign correspondents

value.def: A dean is an important official at a university or college.

example.ex: She was Dean of the Science faculty at Sophia University.
example.tran: 她是上智大学科学院的院长。

value.def: A dean is a priest who is the main administrator of a large church.

example.ex: ...Alan Webster, former Dean of St Paul's.
example.tran: 艾伦·韦伯斯特，圣保罗大教堂前教长

value.def: The dean of a group is the most important member of that group.

example.ex: ...Aaron Copland, who was known as the dean of American composers.
example.tran: 阿隆·科普兰，美国最资深的作曲家

trans: 院长助理；院长；副院长；副院長
教导主任；训导主任；学生处处长
教务长；教務長；学术院长
